cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the extension of a decision procedure for hybrid logic with features commonly used in description logics, such as transitivity and relation inclusion assertions. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Description Logics (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the soundness and completeness of a calculus, which relates to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
